.SH "SYNTAX NOMENCLATURE:"
The following syntax nomenclature is used throughout this page:
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBsubcommand\fR \- Required text, exactly as shown\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB[subcommand]\fR \- Optional text, exactly as shown\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB<user\-input>\fR \- User supplied input field\. Required when not contain in [ ]\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB{n}\fR \- A whole number\. Context determines valid range\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB\.\.\.\fR \- Repeating as many iterations as desired, follows the same preceding syntax pattern\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB|\fR \- Separates options in a list\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB[optional|list]\fR \- An optional field, list of valid options\. "" meaning literally no input is also an option with these lists\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB{require|list}\fR \- A required field, list of valid options\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB$null\fR \- \'\', meaning literally no input\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB[\-abcdefg]\fR \- An optional flag field but must start with a \'\-\' and followed by any combination, in any order\. Eg\. \'\-gca\'
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB<guest>\fR \- chyves guest name
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB<pool>\fR \- ZFS pool\. The word "primary" can be used to specify the primary pool\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB<size>\fR \- Whole number with a size suffix in kilobytes (K), megabytes (M), gigabytes (G), or terabytes (T)\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB<resource>\fR \- ISO or UEFI firmware resource name
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBMG\fR \- Multiple guests can be given using commas\. The word "all" can be used to indicate all guests for these commands\.
.
