.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBcreate\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest> create [<size>] [<pool>]\fR
.
.IP
Where \fIguest\fR is a uniquely identifying name used to reference the guest, optionally [\fIsize\fR] is the size of the block device, and optionally [\fIpool\fR] is the pool to create the guest on in multi\-pool configurations\. If [\fIsize\fR] is not supplied, then \'size\' in defaults is used\. If [\fIpool\fR] is not supplied, then the primary pool is used\. A tap interface is added and associated with the bridge set in defaults\. Support for multi\-guest\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBdelete\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG delete [force|keepnet]\fR
.
.IP
Permanently delete a guest from the host\. If the \'force\' keyword is used, then dependent clones are deleted as well\. The \'keepnet\' keyword is used to keep the network associations, this is useful for clones that share the exact properties\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBdisk\fR
.
.IP
See \fIGUEST DISK SUB\-SUB\-COMMANDS\fR section below\.
