\fBchyves <guest> get {<property>|all}\fR
.
.IP
Gets property for guests\. See \fIPROPERTIES\fR section above for more detail\. Use \'chyves list global\' or \'chyves list defaults\' for respective property types\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBreclaim\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG reclaim\fR
.
.IP
Reclaims a guest\'s VMM resources\. This does not delete a guest from the host, it destroys the guest\'s VMM resources (\fBbhyvectl\fR vernacular)\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBrename\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest> rename <new\-guest\-name>\fR
.
.IP
Renames the guest
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBset\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG|global|defaults set [<prop1>=<value>]\.\.\.\fR
.
.IP
Sets ZFS properties for guests\. Using the \fIguest\fR name of \'defaults\' sets the default values for newly created guests\. Using the \fIguest\fR name of \'global\' sets global properties\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBsnapshot\fR
.
.IP
See \fIGUEST SNAPSHOT SUB\-SUB\-COMMANDS\fR section below\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBstart\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG start [<iso>]\fR
.
.IP
Where \fIiso\fR is optionally the name of an ISO resource, this media is ejected after x amounts of boots as set by global or guest property \'eject_iso_on_n_reboot\'\. This command starts bhyveload, grub\-bhyve, and UEFI guests\.
.
.IP
For grub\-bhyve guests if a ISO is supplied, it is assumed to be the installation ISO for whichever OS is set by the \'os\' property\. This means the \fIdevice\.map\fR and the \fIgrub\.cfg\fR files generated reflect booting from the installation CD\. If a non\-booting CD is needed to be attached to a guest using grub\-bhyve, then manually adding a custom PCIDEV device is suggested\. See the \fIpcidev\fR{n}_ property under \fIGuest Properties\fR section for instructions\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBstop\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG stop [force]\fR
.
.IP
Attempts to gracefully stop a guest\. This is effectively like pressing the power button on a computer tower, this means the guest OS determines how to respond\. Running \'\fBpoweroff\fR\' (or the equivalent) will shutdown a guest and the VMM resources are reclaimed\. Using the \fI[force]\fR option forces the guest to stop by running \'\fBkill \-9\fR\' and then reclaiming the guest\'s VMM resources\. \fBUSE EXTREME CAUTION WITH \'\fIforce\fR\' AND ONLY AS A LAST RESORT, THIS CAN CAUSE A CORRUPT OS\fR\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBupgrade\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG upgrade\fR
.
.IP
Upgrades a guest to the latest chyves guest version\. This add, removes, and modifies guest properties to be compatible with the the current version of chyves\. See \'chyves_guest_version\' guest property for details\.
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBunset\fR
.
.IP
\fBchyves <guest>|MG|all unset <property>\fR
.
.IP
Only the following properties may be removed from guests:
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBeject_iso_on_n_reboot\fR
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBpcidev_{n}\fR
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBvirtio_block_options_disk{n}\fR
.
